SUMMARY:Scandinavian Showcase with an Irish Twist presented by Seattle Folklore Society & Skandia
DESCRIPTION:Mira\, Elise & Pat perform traditional Nordic fiddle tunes that transport listeners and dancers to far-off lands real and imagined. Mira Dickey (hardingfele and fiddle)\, Elise Snoey (fiddle and hardingfele)\, and Patrick Gunning (guitars and fiddle) bring vibrant harmonies and driving groove to timeless music. Sølvstål | Silversteel is a new project from hardanger fiddle player Mira Dickey and viola d’amore and fiddle player Lennart Jansson exploring the novel musical territory at the intersection of Norwegian fiddling and Irish traditional music.   \nSFS and Skandia Folkdance Society are thrilled to co-sponsor and showcase 2 local Scandinavian music bands for this concert. These dynamic young performers have a way of bringing the music to life!  \nThe doors open at 7 pm for the 7:30 pm concert in the Community Hall (lower Brick building).  \nAdvance tickets available now\, $2 more for adults at the door. (Discounts for SFS\, PNA\, & Skandia members\, students\, seniors 65+/ special $10 price for youth up to 17)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/scandinavian-showcase-with-an-irish-twist-presented-by-seattle-folklore-society-skandia/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/25110150/3-21-26-Bands-3.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Folklore Society Concerts":MAILTO:concerts@seafolklore.org
END:VEVENT
